                                    <component>Web</component>
                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14720" author="prozz" created="Mon, 19 Sep 2005 01:01:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;is:&lt;br/&gt;
Can do this in buildPdfDocument, because document is already opened and my event will not trigger.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;should be:&lt;br/&gt;
Can do this in buildPdfDocument, &lt;em&gt;but&lt;/em&gt; document is already opened and my event will not trigger.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;sorry for that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14724" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Mon, 19 Sep 2005 03:02:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing this out! I&apos;ve added the following callback method to AbstractPdfView:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  protected void prepareWriter(Map model, PdfWriter writer, HttpServletRequest request)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;which will be called right before &quot;buildPdfMetadata&quot;, i.e before the &quot;Document.open()&quot; call.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
